A lawyer for a notorious Dartmouth College fraternity accused of branding new members on their body compared it to a form of self-expression like piercing or tattooing.

Alpha Delta - depicted in the 1978 film Animal House - was suspended in October for various incidents including hazing, serving alcohol to minors and hosting unregistered parties.

Officials are now extending that punishment over new allegations that members were burned last fall, with one student reportedly having the skin on his buttocks seared.

They are also considering closing the 46-year-old club for good depending on the outcome of discussions. 

