Attorney George Ostler confirmed a small number of fraternity members voluntarily chose to get body brands, but the practice was never a condition of membership.

He says no hazing occurred, no one was injured and members are cooperating fully with the college.

News of the branding incident emerged this week via the website Gawker.

A sophomore pledge of Alpha Delta reportedly agreed to be branded on his backside in the fall of 2014, according to a tipster.

By agreeing to the branding, the pledge would theoretically be allowed to avoid 'more drinking-intensive pledge activities'. 

When the pledge went home for winter break, he realized something was wrong with his brand and went to the doctor, Gawker reported.

